.env
    *.db
    *.pem
    __pycache__/
    *.docx
    *.zip
    ```
3.  Remove the sensitive files from the Git index (this won't delete them from your computer):
    
```bash
    git rm -r --cached backend/.env backend/vault.db backend/*.pem backend/__pycache__
    git commit -m "Remove sensitive files and binaries from tracking"
    ```

### Why the "fish" errors happened?
It looks like you copied the Markdown formatting (the backticks 
``` and the bullet points) into your terminal. The `fish` shell tried to execute those words as commands. Only copy the specific lines starting with `git`.

